      "content": "Even one glass of wine can interact with zolpidem in ways that are not just \"a little more sleepy.\" Combining depressants like alcohol and sleep aids can dangerously slow down your central nervous system. Instead of risking an unpredictable reaction, try a warm bath or some deep breathing exercises to calm your system before taking your prescribed dose. If you are still struggling, try taking the medication exactly as directed, without any alcohol interference.",
      "source": "target",
